SUMMARY

The Financial Sector, Housing Markets and the 
Impact on Urban Development in Germany

by Katrin Klein-Hitpass

Due to new financial market instruments real 
estate became an international tradable invest­
ment good and yield oriented investors from the 
financial sector gained increasing influence on 
the housing market development. In addition pri­
vate households increasingly invest in housing as 
a strategy to provide for one's old age and indivi­
dual risks such as unemployment. Using the ex­
ample of Berlin the paper illustrates the effects 
different investment motives and strategies have 
on the development of the housing market.

Geographische Rundschau 2 I 2015 25

